description:
Ever dream of sailing off into the sunset on your own sailboat?  ‘Sailing Nervous’ is the story of two novice sailors - married for 30 years -  searching for freedom and fun by facing obstacles, overcoming fear, and learning to sail to different shores. The 'Sailing Nervous' series will trace their progress as they attempt to make their dream a reality. From dreaming of sailing, to learning how to sail, to buying a boat, to fixing the boat up for sailing, and then finally beginning their journey aboard, they invite you to come along.  

Episodes will be posted every Friday at 12:00 noon  (Eastern standard time - USA) 

Thanks for subscribing!

description:
This channel is more then just about sailing... It's about 2 young people that fell in love and worked hard to accomplish their dream.
After building their sailboat they sailed off into the sunset. 30 + years later they are still living their dream! Come sail with us! Explore exotic places and see how we made it possible. We've lived off the grid for the last 30 years for no more then poverty wages. We built  Emerald Steel  and have been living aboard and cruising most of the time since her completion in 1987. Suzie did all of the welding and Jules did all the cutting, grinding and fitting. We were 23 and 36 years old at the beginning of our project in 1985.  Our general daily electrical usage is provided by 2- 80 watt solar panels. We also have a 7 kw diesel generator which powers our 1000 gal. per day water maker - designed and built by Jules  (although we only use 10 gal per day), hydraulic windlass for our 1/2" chain ,mig welder and plasma cutter which we carry on board.

description: We are Jeremiah, Brittany, our kids and our dogs! A family that are selling everything that we own, buying a sailboat, moving aboard and sailing away through the Florida Keys, Bahamas, the Caribbean and then who knows where else!  Maybe the Atlantic Circle or maybe we will go west! Follow along with us, we will be uploading videos often about our journey, adventures along the way and our lifestyle! You can also view us on our blog at www.lazygeckos.net and on Facebook at Lazy Gecko Sailing!

description:
All about Sailing, Simplicity & the Pursuit of Happiness w/ Teresa Carey & Ben Eriksen.  Sailing adventures aboard a Nor'sea 27, a Bristol Channel Cutter 28, and now a Norseman 447. 

Our first film One Simple Question is being released in 2015 (finally). Our new project Hello Ocean, is an ocean conservation sailing adventure that strives to drive a pro ocean message into mainstream media. 2015 promises more videos here!

In an effort to sustain our lifestyle, and help fund Hello Ocean, we started a sail training business. Our combined 45 years and 75,000 miles of sailing experience along with many years in education help us offer an intense and intimate learning environment.
title: Sailing Simplicity

description:
Welcome to the Sailing Adventures of Pirate Booty. 

In 2013 I  found 'Pirate Booty' a 32' 1987 Sidelman  295 32' Sailboat' abandoned in Miami, FL    She was in less than Perfect Shape.  
 She has a 13 HP Internal Yanmar Diesel and 5 Sails, 8' Beam and was in need of much work.  I have taken her out on a few trial runs, she is a Dream.

 I want to share all the Restoration Work I do with you, the other Dreamers who want boats of their own!  This is my 3rd Sailboat I have restored. I want to save you $$ and get your Dreams Going by my video's and examples and show what many don't or I could never find and had to create. 

This Sailboat in the end cost me 0 Dollars.  Through it being abandoned, the owner missing, I tracked it back though owners until I found one.  She signed the boat over to me for free!

Follow and Subscribe as I redo her Electrical, Plumbing, Wood Work and Rigging. 

This will prepare me for my next  Dream ... Get her all Ship Shape and Sail to the Bahamas !
title: Kelly Williamson

description:
This channel was designed to capture and document my sailing adventure from Canada to Australia, I started filming the preparation from the moment I purchased Willow, a 1986 Windward sloop. There is a lots of footage on this channel that is recording my day to day life within the preparation, this is primarily to stay in contact with my friends and family back in Australia.
In saying that, I welcome people to subscribe and join me on this adventure of a lifetime, I can't promise perfect editing, but I can promise to be myself and to face the challengers of boat preparation and sailing with you, 

Thank you!

description:
Hi and welcome to fun N stuff with the Foxwells

We are a family of three with Ian playing the role of Dad. Hannah being Mum and Elizabeth being, well, just Izzy. Plus special guest appearances by our toy poodle Winnie (thats Winnie the Poo....dle)

We live, work and sail on the east coast of England and this channel is a collection of films showing our life as it happens.

We hope you enjoy it, and if you do tell your friends.

description: I've always loved the ocean and it was probably inevitable that someday I'd buy a sailboat.  In the Spring of 2013 I was fortunate to spend about a week on a private yacht in the Med and the experience rekindled my love of boats. I began looking for a boat in earnest in July 2013 and in September 2013 I bought a 1980 Cabo Rico 38.  S/V Corsair will be berthed in Southern Maryland near Washington DC from where I will sail the Chesapeake Bay as much as possible while continuing to work for the next 3-5 years.  Beyond that, who knows?  I hope I will be able to sail away someday soon.  I will be posting regular and hopefully progressively better video updates as we complete final prep, launch the boat and begin sailing the Chesapeake and beyond.  Please join me on the adventure by subscribing.
title: The Corsair

description:
My husband was diagnosed with Mantle Cell Lymphoma one year ago.  This was a major turning point in our life where we realized we were only living this day to get to the next.  Something needed to change, especially if he only had a short amount of time left.  We made the crazy decision that we want to sail around the world and this is our story as it happens.

Our immediate goal is to fix up the sailboat we have now (pearson 30) and sell her to buy a larger vessel on the ocean.  We will fix up this second vessel and then hopefully untie the lines and set sail with the world in front of us.  We are pretty crafty when it comes to pinching pennies and it is also a goal to do this as cheap as possible.  I hope we can all learn together!
title: Hitchhikers GuideToSailing

description: This channel is to document our sailing adventure aboard our 42' catamaran that included preparing her for a life back at sea. When we found her, she'd spent years in a boatyard, alone and neglected. But we've changed all that - we've replaced all the standing rigging; outfitted her with all new electronics and bottom paint; serviced and inspected every system on board - all in preparation for the adventure of a lifetime.  Follow along as we set sail on a journey to catch some rays (and try to have as much fun as possible along the way.) Warning: you must have a sense of humor to enjoy this series.

description:
Sailrite is a second generation family business. Founded in 1969 the business was intended to serve a function no other business had ever served as a source of instruction and materials for amateur sailmakers. At that time the very concept of "amateur sailmaking" was new. Sailmaking was generally believed a black art. Sailrite has largely changed this view and today is well known as a provider of sail kits to serious racers, boat builders and sailors owning good old boats. These individuals build sails to broaden their self-reliance and power their boats. Sailmaking is a great deal of fun and a very satisfying hobby. 

Sailrite is a full-stock retailer of thousands of canvas supplies, tools, fabrics, kits, and videos including the Ultrafeed LSZ-1 sewing machine and complete Sunbrella fabric lines. Sailrite can help you learn more, spend less, and do-it-yourself.
title: Sailrite

description:
This is a site all about small boat cruising on a catamaran. We hope to inspire you to go out cruising by sharing our experience of building our catamaran and our sailing adventures from Vancouver, Canada to Mexico across the Pacific ocean to Hawaii and back to Vancouver as well as the cruising ground of the Pacific Northwest.16 years ago and have sailed it. We hope to see you out there.

Sincerely, Garett and Carllie

description:
Forespar is a company in which a team of dedicated boaters has continually advanced the quality of the sailing and powerboating experience since 1967. Founded by life-long boater Robert Foresman, the company has pursued his philosophy of innovation and quality to produce unique products which fill real needs.
 
 
Today, the crew at Forespar oversees a multifaceted design, manufacturing and worldwide distribution system from its modern headquarters in Southern California using CAD/CAM design , full machine shop, 80’ spray paint booth, plastic injection molding and carbon composite processing.
 
Forespar, along with its other widely recognized branded products including Leisure Furl, and Marelon, can be counted on by boaters to provide value and many years of enjoyment and performance. We are always leaders and innovaters; never followers and we strive to serve every boater.
 
We invite you to visit our website www.forespar.com, and join our Facebook Fan Page.

description:
Welcome to my channel dedicated to sailing.

Back in 2006 the wife and I noticed our business was falling off. By late 2007 it was apparent that we were headed into a recession. We researched a LOT and came to the conclusion that things were starting to fail. We made a decision to buy a sailboat, learn to sail, pay off all debt and move aboard. Our idea was that from then on we should just invest what we had into tangibles for our retirement instead of giving our money to a bank/broker/investor that would end up stealing or losing it.

We're over half way to our goal. We live aboard 50% of the time. Our money does not go into an account to be lost or devalued by our government/banking system, but into our sailboat and food supplies that will last us months, if not years. We plan to sail south into the Pacific and island hop. We will farm the sea, fish, grow food here and there, barter services, and visit islands.

Come join us while we learn and ready ourselves for our voyage!
title: Tom SailBeforeSunset

description: After five years of saving and scheming, we quit our jobs in May of 2014 and sold our house in Denver, CO. We're cruising aboard a small sailboat, Baby Blue, an Allied Luders 33' sloop. By living simply, we hope to stretch our funds in the cruising kitty to keep us afloat for at least a couple of years. We're currently in Grenada where we will wait out hurricane season before heading back out into the open ocean. Check out our blog at feedingthecruisingkitty.blogspot.com for the whole story!

description:
We are an Australian couple with a yacht - 43.4 ft Beneteau Cyclades - and the intentions of circumnavigating the globe... Initially having no clue of how to sail! We started in the Mediterranean, recently crossed the Atlantic Ocean and are finally in the beautiful sunny Caribbean. We started making movies to share our adventure with friends and family back in Australia, and now we continue to make to share our adventure with the world. With your support we can keep the movies coming! We are so glad to have you onboard as the adventure unfolds.

-Please become a Patron!
You are helping to keep our dream alive.

description:
Albin Vega 27 Velocir is home to     the Captains Howerton. We are a young couple navigating the cruising lifestyle as we sail throughout warm waters.

We do our blog not just as a way of keeping in touch with family and friends, but because we enjoyed so many other blogs during our two years working, saving and outfitting Velocir.  We found their insight not only entertaining and useful but inspiring.

For our full blog please visit www.velocir.com

description:
My name is Alex Dorsey. I'm a film maker that got fed up with the industry and wanted to do something a little different. I bought a small sail boat and decided to document my experiences cruising. In the last 5 years I've sailed from Mystic Connecticut, 1000 miles down the ICW, through the Bahamas, Jamaica, and across the Caribbean to Cartagena Colombia. After that I produced my first film in the Project BlueSphere series "California to Colombia". 

After that I lived in the San Blas Islands of Panama with the Kuna Indians for a year before transiting the Panama Canal and single handing my 28' sailboat "Namaste" 8000 miles across the Pacific to Brisbane Australia "What a ride"! 

If you would like more information please check out www.projectbluesphere.com. From my website you can read daily logs, check out pictures and video clips, or buy my DVD's. 

Cheers guys!

Alex Dorsey
www.projectbluesphere.com

description:
This channel is dedicated to documenting our experiences from purchasing, learning to sail Southern Cross sailing on the Pacific Ocean and eventually moving full time onto her to sail the world. We want to share our experiences with everyone who has dreamed of a life on the water. We have learned a lot of valuable information along the way with little guidance and know how intimidating of a process it can be. Our plan is to do a Pacific crossing from San Diego to the Southern Islands and after that who knows where we will end up.
 
.
  Southern Cross is a 1983 O'Day 39  built in Fall River, MA and is a USCG Documented Vessel. She turns salt water into fresh water and produces her own electricity. Join our adventure! Please subscribe and follow us on Facebook for continuing updates


Thanks again and enjoy.
S/V Southern Cross & Crew
https://twitter.com/svsoutherncross
https://www.google.com/+SVSouthernCross
https://www.facebook.com/pages/SV-Southern-Cross/600832790017022

description:
Welcome to the Sailing Monea youtube channel!

Here you can follow our adventures aboard Monea sailing the Luleå archipelago, Bothnian bay, Sweden.

We are not circumnavigators, salty pirates or full time live-aboards. We are merely a couple who just bought a small cruiser and loves to sail. Our contribution to the worldwide sailing community will be to tell you about the wonderful Luleå archipelago situated just south of the polar circle. We would love to see more international cruisers in our waters and therefore we will post videos of us sailing under the mythical midnight sun and anchoring at some of the most popular Islands. Hopefully this will inspire you to discover the Luleå archipelago yourself.

Welcome!

/Frida & P-A

description: Greetings and welcome to Iandi Boats.  I am a professional builder and have recently become a sailor and nautical designer.  I decided to dedicate myself to sailing and the design, construction and improvement of sailing vessels.  This channel will be dedicated to my journey into sailing, boat design and construction.  Sit back and follow me on my journey.  I hope you learn something new and are inspired to share with all who watch.  Until next time... Peace and Blessings  :-)  Kamau

description:
More Hands On Deck is a quest for a better life full of adventure. We travel the world by sailboat connecting with other cultures and nature. We want to achieve seemingly unreachable goals and instill the idea that any goal or dream, no matter how large or improbable it may seem, can be realized with hard work, dedication, and the willingness to take risks. Through this we hope to spread an awareness of the magnificent beauty of the earth and the life that exists within. We hope our journey inspires you to get outside and explore our beautiful world.

Locations will include: 

Mexico, Guatemala, Nicaragua, Costa Rica and Panama. Plus with your support, weather and boat permitting, we could add even more phenomenal locations such as The Galapagos, The Marquesa Islands, Fiji and Australia 

We love what we do and we would love your support so we can keep making videos for your enjoyment!
 Become a patron @ www.patreon.com/morehandsondeck


See more at www.MoreHandsOnDeck.com

Sebastian set foot on the first sailboat when he was about 13 years and has raced for several years, including a Elvtröm 717 - One Off, and an International 806. If, however, had a break of 10 years.

description: We offer a full range of courses from Basic Sailing through Ocean Training Cruises on Island Packet yachts in Chesapeake Bay, Virgin Islands and the Atlantic Ocean between Norfolk, Bermuda and the Caribbean. Also Celestial and Coastal Navigation classes online line and Docking Practice classes. Students can earn certification from the American Sailing Association (ASA). We've been doing this continuously since 1991, and have graduated over 11,000 students from the various levels of our program, and completed over 240 ocean training cruises of between 400 and 1500 miles each. Refer to http://www.mdschool.com/Why.htm for a further description.

description:
Join us, James & Angela, and take a glimpse into our lives aboard our Westsail 32 sailboat. 
We will feature the joys and challenges of living aboard, the ongoing projects, our plans and goals, and little adventures.

Having purchased the boat of our dreams and moved aboard in the past year, we are still new to this life and eager to share it with others!
title: Through the Portlight

description:
White Spots are undiscovered areas on each individual's personal map of life. These are not necessarily places you want to go, but can be any kind of dream that you want to come true.

The purpose of WhiteSpotPirates (WSP) is to bring people one step closer to putting their own dreams into reality, to build up a community that inspires and supports each other. 

The weekly video documentation "Untie The Lines" is WSP's first project. It is about a young woman who bought an old sailing boat in Panama and wants to try and sail the word. Future plans of WSP are to feature different stories of a wide range of "Pirates".

Become a Patron (www.patreon.com/WhiteSpotPirates) of UNTIE THE LINES now or use PayPal (https://www.paypal.com/cgi-bin/webscr?cmd=_s-xclick&hosted_button_id=GWBYVNU5LENLS) to support this project. Thank you so much!
title: WhiteSpotPirates

description:
Harken Inc. is a leading manufacturer and marketer of quality sailboat hardware and accessories.  Harken gear has dominated such events as the America's Cup and Olympics.  Our blocks, travelers, furling systems and winches can be found aboard everything form the smallest dinghies to the largest megayachts and cruisers.

Headquarted in Pewaukee, Wisconsin, Harken manufactures in the  USA and Italy.  Its network includes offices in 48 countries, with group offices located in Australia, France, Italy, New Zealand, Poland, Sweden, the United Kingdom, and the United States (Rhode Island, California, and Florida).

description:
The Subway Sailor Channel is a channel created by a regular New York City working person, with a high level of ambition and curiosity towards sailing and crossing the Atlantic Ocean. 

I purchased a Southern Cross 28, a pocket cruiser that has been around the world, and decided that I would fix it up and take it somewhere far in order to have a great time and accomplish my goal of eventually crossing the Atlantic back home to Spain.  Follow me in order to get things done.

description:
I have a story to tell! - It is about the wide oceans, and narrow rivers I have crossed and followed. In 2010 I left my homeport Hamburg in Germany to set out for a cruise to distant shores. Here I am going to tell about this trip that has brought me into the jungle of central america, to canada and deep into the US Mid-West and South.

Here you will find a mix of sailing and inland adventures combined with stories from locals I meet along the route.

description: Welcome! We are Tate and Dani, two crazy 30 somethings who are planning a hopeful circumnavigation starting January 2015.  Just as soon as we finish our 4 year complete refit of our 1974 Westsail 32 "Sundowner" we'll quit our jobs and head out into the wild blue yonder. It's all coming together here in New Orleans, La.  Here you will find a collection of home videos we create along the way.  Glad to have you aboard!

description:
We are Drake and Monique cruising aboard our Westsail 42 sailboat and home 'Paragon.'   

We are devoted to exploring the world by sail and have big plans to bring you videos each week that tell stories about the cruising life. We are focused on offshore sailing, living aboard, cultural immersion, friendship, and adventure!   Join us as we sail from North Carolina to Canada, Greenland, Iceland, the Faroe Islands, Scotland and Ireland and explore many exciting ports along the way.  

Please visit our our social media pages listed below to keep up with our latest news.   We love your comments, and always try to respond to as many as we can.  

Our videos would not be possible without your support.  If you are enjoying them, then please consider helping us with our video production expenses via the Patreon or Paypal links below.   Any contribution is greatly appreciated. Thank you for sailing with us!

description:
We are Drake and Monique sailing around the world aboard our 42 foot sailboat and home 'Paragon.' 

Here on youtube.com/ParagonSkies, we will be publishing aerial videos of the places we have sailed to.

See our story and our other 'cruising life' videos on our other channel youtube.com/DrakeParagon.

If you are enjoying our aerial videos, then consider helping us with our video production expenses by becoming a ParagonSkies Patreon supporter at http://www.patreon.com/ParagonSkies  Or you can also help us out by sending us a Paypal donation at https://www.paypal.com/cgi-bin/webscr?cmd=_donations&business=DrakeParagon%40gmail%2ecom&lc=US&item_name=ParagonSkies%20%2d%20Aerial%20videos%20from%20all%20over%20the%20world&currency_code=USD&bn=PP%2dDonationsBF%3abtn_donateCC_LG%2egif%3aNonHosted

description:
We are Shaun and Julia, a Canadian couple with a dream of sailing the world and making documentaries of the cruising lifestyle for your enjoyment!

We took the first big step towards our dream in 2014 by purchasing a 1976 Bayfield 25 sailboat named I’m Easy in Parry Sound, Ontario and will be spending the next few years fixing and re-fitting it as we sail through the Great Lakes, down the canal system and all the way to the Caribbean!

We would love for you to follow us on our journeys!

description:
One blistery winter morning four years ago, Erik and Meagan stumbled onto a plan... two boats, several uninsured surgeries, countless unforgettable friendships, and a whole lot of work later they, along with their furry companion, Nikka, finally sailed out under the Golden Gate Bridge and turned left.  Traveling South along the west coast of the Americas, and then on to ...?  Your guess is as good as theirs, maybe they’ll sail over to Hawaii, maybe sail around the world.
 
They once heard a wise man say “routine is the time killer,” and they took it to heart.  They are sailing the Pacific Ocean attempting to live every day with their eyes open and minds engaged.  For the first time living each day excited about the possibility of tomorrow instead of dreading or trying to control it.
 
Follow them along on their journey and share in their joys and challenges and see where their crazy sailing adventure lands them.

description:
Nicole and Steve Graham are natural adventurers who've recently and spontaneously purchased and moved aboard a 41' sailboat, named 'Two Little Birds'. They currently live in Fairhope, AL with plans to sail the Caribbean in October 2015. These episodes are to firstly inform all of the family and friends who have supported them on their journey as to what they have been up to. Also to educate, inspire and entertain others sailors, live aboards, and anyone who will listen to all that comes with living on a boat. This is all new to Steve and Nicole as well so we will all just learn together as we go. 

Website: www.travelgraham.com
Instagram: @travelgraham

description:
About
We LOVE sailing, We LOVE travelling, and we LOVE making videos about it. Delos is a 53 foot sailboat home to young adventurous souls sailing around the world! Welcome aboard!

Mission
It’s simple really- we just want to make you SMILE! We do this because we LOVE it. Given our short time on this AMAZING PLANET there’s absolutely, positively, nothing more we’d rather be doing with our time! We hope by sharing this adventure you will find some inspiration in your life.

Description
Delos is a 53 foot Amel Super Maramu. She was built in La Rochelle France in 2000 and has since seen what most sailboats dream of seeing. She has completed a circumnavigation and is now on her second voyage around the world. She is a sailing ketch (2 masts) and has enough room to comfortably sleep 6 people. Delos is able to turn salt water into fresh water, sun into energy, provide food and shelter, travel for months on end without visiting a dock and best of all, be the place we call home.

description:
We are a family of nine that believe there is more to life than careers, houses and cars. That if you live simply, have an advetureous spirit and a dash of crazy you can experience places that most only dream of.

Three years ago we sold our house along with most we owned and bought a sailboat in San Fransisco. We sailed her to Alaska and have been living aboard while we work to fund our upcoming adventures. Our dream is to cast off the lines and see the world. 

We hope to document our advetures through video so others can join us on our wanderings.
